      • decorate

        public static boolean decorate(World world,
                               java.util.Random rand,
                               ChunkPos chunkPos,
                               BlockPos placementPos,
                               DecorateBiomeEvent.Decorate.EventType type)
        Use this method when there is a specific BlockPos location given for decoration. If only the chunk position is available, use #decorate(World, Random, ChunkPos, Decorate.EventType) instead.
        Parameters:
        world - the world being generated in
        rand - the random generator used for decoration
        chunkPos - the original chunk position used for generation, passed to the decorator
        placementPos - the specific position used for generating a feature, somewhere in the 2x2 chunks used for decoration
        type - the type of decoration
